<section class="labs gap-bottom-xsmall">

    <div class="row headline">
        <div class="columns">
            <h1 class="text-center size-large gap-top-medium gap-bottom-small">
                Convert Excel to Handsontable
                <sup class="beta"><small>BETA</small></sup><br/>
                <span>The easiest way to create a configuration file</span>
            </h1>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="large-8 large-centered columns">
            <div class="uploader text-center">
                <p>Drop your spreadsheet here</p>
                <p>or</p>
                <a href="#" class="btn size-medium bg-blue bg-lighten text-white shadow">Choose file</a>
                <p>XLSX, XLS, CSV. Max. 2MB</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row spreadsheet-samples gap-top-small">
        <div class="columns">
            <h2 class="gap-bottom-xxsmall text-center">Need a sample spreadsheet?<br/>
                <a href="<%= static_path %>/resources/ModLabs/excel-to-handsontable.xlsx">Download test file</a>
            </h2>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="large-5 columns project-description">
            <h3 class="gap-top-xsmall">About project</h3>

            <p>This app enables you to create a Handsontable instance from your existing Excel file. This project
                is nowhere near ready so consider it as a beta version. There are still a lot of limitations of
                what we can read from your spreadsheet file to be represented in Handsontable.</p>
            <p>At this stage it handles formulas, values, and styles.</p>
            <p class="gap-top-xxsmall"><strong>The most important constrains are
                    as following:</strong></p>

            <ul>
                <li>Saving changes (changes will be lost after page reloads)</li>
                <li>Cross-sheet functions</li>
                <li>Special functions: lookup, vlookup, today() and similar</li>
                <li>Named ranges</li>
                <li>Borders width (borders will be converted into 1px)</li>
                <li>Clockwise/counterwise text rotation</li>
                <li>Macros</li>
                <li>Indentation</li>
                <li>Invisible borders</li>
                <li>Toolbar and formula bar</li>
                <li>Filters control within cells</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="large-6 columns">
            <div class="row subscribe-form">
                <h3 class="gap-top-xsmall">Subscribe to updates</h3>
                <div id="mc_embed_signup">
